data.text:
About Unchagaon

Unchagaon is a Village in Kairana Block in Muzaffarnagar District of Uttar Pradesh State, India. It belongs to Saharanpur Division . It is located 55 KM towards west from District head quarters Muzaffarnagar. 10 KM from Kairana Rural. 538 KM from State capital Lucknow

Unchagaon Pin code is 247774 and postal head office is Kairana .

Jharkheri ( 2 KM ) , Aldi ( 3 KM ) , Gujarpur ( 3 KM ) , Asadpur ( 3 KM ) , Dudhar ( 3 KM ) are the nearby Villages to Unchagaon. Unchagaon is surrounded by Kandhla Block towards East , Bapoli Block towards west , Shamli Block towards East , Chhaprauli Block towards South .

Shamli , Panipat , Samalkha , Gharaunda are the near by Cities to Unchagaon.

This Place is in the border of the Muzaffarnagar District and Panipat District. Panipat District Bapoli is west towards this place . Also it is in the Border of other district Baghpat . It is near to the Haryana State Border.

Unchagaon 2011 Census Details

Unchagaon Local Language is Hindi. Unchagaon Village Total population is 5223 and number of houses are 899. Female Population is 45.1%. Village literacy rate is 66.5% and the Female Literacy rate is 25.6%.
